questions.question_text:
You have modified your Terraform configuration to fix a typo in the Terraform ID of a resource from aws_security_group.http to aws_security_group.http
//IMG//

Which of the following commands would you run to update the ID in state without destroying the resource?

discussion.content:
I think B is correct as you are configuring the provider not declaring it

terraform {
 required_providers {
 aws = {
 source = "hashicorp/aws"
 version = "~> 4.0"
 }
 }
}

# Configure the AWS Provider
provider "aws" {
 region = "us-east-1"
}

The question seems to hinge on the word "needs" ... if it was asking for "required_providers" then they would need to nested inside a terraform block however none of the examples show the correct syntax for a required_providers block

terraform {
 required_providers {
 mycloud = {
 source = "mycorp/mycloud"
 version = "~> 1.0"
 }
 }
}

I'm going with B.

